data.name: label7.Text
data.value: The Regional Transport Office or Regional Transport Authority (RTO / RTA) is the organisation of the Indian government responsible for maintaining a database of drivers and a database of vehicles for various states of South Africa. The RTO issues driving licences, organises collection of vehicle excise duty (also known as road tax and road fund licence) and sells personalised registrations.

data.value: NB! This application is only responsible for learners that already have K53 knowledge and that are over 18 years of age to take digital assessment. Due to the corona-virus of 2019 regulations learner's are not allowed to take any in-contact tests.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: The New Official K53 Manual is a comprehensive and effective guide to passing your Learner's Licence and K53 Driver's Licence - first time. Covering both light and heavy motor vehicles, and motorcycles, each chapter discusses the knowledge and skills expected of you.
